    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Targeting the country’s 13 high-risk districts, the program focuses on  training public health care providers and female community health  volunteers, improving diagnosis and access to treatment, monitoring drug  resistance and updating national antimalaria drug policy. The grant  focuses on procuring and distributing long-lasting insecticidal nets,  implementing behavior change communication strategies, and capacity  building."
